# Build context is the repo root (Dockerfile at apps/web/Dockerfile). The image
# does a fresh `pnpm install`, so none of these are needed in the context — and
# excluding them keeps the ACR upload small.
**/node_modules
.git
.gitignore
**/.next
**/.expo
.claude
**/coverage
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/build
**/*.log
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
# Terraform artifacts: gitignored (infra/azure/.gitignore) so they don't show in
# `git status` and the clean-tree gate can't catch them — exclude them here so
# `az acr build .` never uploads local plan/state/tfvars (which can hold SECRETS)
# to the ACR build context. The image only needs app/package sources, not infra/.
**/.terraform/
**/*.tfstate*
**/*.tfplan
**/tfplan
infra/azure/tfplan
**/*.tfvars
**/.DS_Store
